### parseBackslash() {#abba3a1b37c8d40cefcab729ee016441d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static size&#95;t parseBackslash (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> Src, size&#95;t I, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallstring">SmallString</a>&lt; 128 &gt; &amp; Token)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Backslashes are interpreted in a rather complicated way in the Windows-style command line, because backslashes are used both to separate path and to escape double quote.

This method consumes runs of backslashes as well as the following double quote if it&#39;s escaped.


<ul>
<li>If an even number of backslashes is followed by a double quote, one backslash is output for every pair of backslashes, and the last double quote remains unconsumed. The double quote will later be interpreted as the start or end of a quoted string in the main loop outside of this function.</li>
<li>If an odd number of backslashes is followed by a double quote, one backslash is output for every pair of backslashes, and a double quote is output for the last pair of backslash-double quote. The double quote is consumed in this case.</li>
<li>Otherwise, backslashes are interpreted literally.</li>
</ul>

Definition at line <a href="#l00899">899</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/commandline-cpp">CommandLine.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00881" /><CodeLine lineNumber="881"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00882" /><CodeLine lineNumber="882"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Backslashes are interpreted in a rather complicated way in the Windows-style</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00883" /><CodeLine lineNumber="883"><Highlight kind="comment">/// command line, because backslashes are used both to separate path and to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00884" /><CodeLine lineNumber="884"><Highlight kind="comment">/// escape double quote. This method consumes runs of backslashes as well as the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00885" /><CodeLine lineNumber="885"><Highlight kind="comment">/// following double quote if it&#39;s escaped.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00886" /><CodeLine lineNumber="886"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00887" /><CodeLine lineNumber="887"><Highlight kind="comment">///  &#42; If an even number of backslashes is followed by a double quote, one</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00888" /><CodeLine lineNumber="888"><Highlight kind="comment">///    backslash is output for every pair of backslashes, and the last double</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00889" /><CodeLine lineNumber="889"><Highlight kind="comment">///    quote remains unconsumed. The double quote will later be interpreted as</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00890" /><CodeLine lineNumber="890"><Highlight kind="comment">///    the start or end of a quoted string in the main loop outside of this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00891" /><CodeLine lineNumber="891"><Highlight kind="comment">///    function.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00892" /><CodeLine lineNumber="892"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00893" /><CodeLine lineNumber="893"><Highlight kind="comment">///  &#42; If an odd number of backslashes is followed by a double quote, one</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00894" /><CodeLine lineNumber="894"><Highlight kind="comment">///    backslash is output for every pair of backslashes, and a double quote is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00895" /><CodeLine lineNumber="895"><Highlight kind="comment">///    output for the last pair of backslash-double quote. The double quote is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00896" /><CodeLine lineNumber="896"><Highlight kind="comment">///    consumed in this case.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00897" /><CodeLine lineNumber="897"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00898" /><CodeLine lineNumber="898"><Highlight kind="comment">///  &#42; Otherwise, backslashes are interpreted literally.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00899" /><CodeLine lineNumber="899" lineLink="#abba3a1b37c8d40cefcab729ee016441d"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">size&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="#abba3a1b37c8d40cefcab729ee016441d">parseBackslash</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> Src, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">size&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I</a>, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallstring">SmallString&lt;128&gt;</a> &amp;Token) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00900" /><CodeLine lineNumber="900"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">size&#95;t</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#abb2b3a60ccc38a28239e19a1646e0c8a">E</a> = Src.size();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00901" /><CodeLine lineNumber="901"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">int</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> BackslashCount = 0;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00902" /><CodeLine lineNumber="902"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Skip the backslashes.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="903"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">do</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
